The Church of Englands old antithesis to new Arminianisme VVhere in 7. anti-Arminian orthodox tenents, are euidently proued; their 7. opposite Arminian (once popish and Pelagian) errors are manifestly disproued, to be the ancient, established, and vndoubted doctrine of the Church of England; by the concurrent testimony of the seuerall records and writers of our Church, from the beginning of her reformation, to this present. By William Prynne Gent. Hospitij Lincolniensis. Prynne, William, 1600-1669.
[56], 140 p.
[Printed by Augustine Mathewes and Elizabeth Allde for Michael Sparke], London : 1629.
Printers' and bookseller's names from STC. Mathewes probably printed A⁴ a-c⁴ B-G⁴. Probably issued with his "God, no impostor nor deluder" (STC 20460). Reproduction of the original in the Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery.
